SUMMARY:Third Sat. Contra Dance
DESCRIPTION:Contra Dancing\nThis is a no-official-host dance to live music at the Fulton Community Center\, 68 SW Miles Street in Portland. All are welcome.\n\nMusic tonight from Peter and the Wolf Tones (George Penk on fiddle\, Heather Pinney on piano\, Jesse Schafer on cello) with caller Shell Stowell. Lesson for newcomers at 7 pm\, dancing from 7:30 to 10:30 with a short break halfway through.\n\nBring water\, clothing appropriate for indoor aerobic activity and smooth-soled shoes for dancing. Please do *not* wear scented products to the dance.\n\nCost: suggested entry of $15 helps us break even\; sliding scale is available. Cash\, check or card.\n\nMask policy: recommended but not required. For more information about PCDC\, go to: www.portlandcountrydance.org. *[Note: there are always plenty of folks on the dance floor regardless of how many sign up via Meetup.]*
